This paper deals with a data structure problem involving sets and operations such as search, split, merge, make-set, and shift. This suggests that it belongs to the category of data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the problem is related to compressed texts (Lempel-Ziv), which suggests that it could also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of biased search trees in the solution suggests that it could also belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or algorithms and data structures (cs.DM). Finally, the use of amortized analysis suggests that it could also belong to the category of complexity theory (cs.CC).
